The paper deals with the power control problem in visible light communication, which is a subfield of communication systems (cs.COMM) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) is a key aspect of the paper, which falls under information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the optimization problem and the use of simulation results suggest that the paper may also fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
